This is a textbook case of **coverage-without-verification**. Every method is called (→ 95% line coverage), but almost no test checks the *outcome*. Here's the severity-ranked audit:

---

## 🔴 CRITICAL — Assert-Free Tests (fire-and-forget)

These tests touch code but verify **nothing**. Any regression passes silently.

### 1. `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)
Calls `AddProduct` but never confirms the product was persisted.
```csharp
// Fix: verify the product is retrievable
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var result = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(result);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", result.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, result.Price);
```

### 2. `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 32)
Calls `UpdatePrice` but never checks the price actually changed. A no-op `Save()` would pass.
```csharp
// Fix: assert the new price
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
```

### 3. `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 38)
Calls `RemoveProduct` but never checks the product is gone.
```csharp
// Fix: confirm deletion
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

### 4. `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)
Calls `GetProductCount` on an **empty** catalog and discards the result. Doesn't test 0, 1, or N.
```csharp
// Fix: assert against known state
Assert.AreEqual(0, _catalog.GetProductCount());
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
Assert.AreEqual(1, _catalog.GetProductCount());
```

### 5. `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 68)
Applies a 10% discount but never verifies any price changed. The core arithmetic (`Price * (1 - fraction)`) is completely untested.
```csharp
// Fix: assert discounted prices
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")!.Price);
```

### 6. `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 84)
Imports CSV but never checks any product was created. Malformed-CSV handling is also untested.
```csharp
// Fix: verify imported product
_catalog.ImportFromCsv("SKU-001,Widget,9.99");
var p = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(p);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", p.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, p.Price);
```

