**Summary:** 6 of 10 tests have **zero assertions**, 4 have only `IsNotNull`. This suite achieves high coverage by *executing* every line but *verifying* almost nothing — the classic "test theater" anti-pattern. Every test needs outcome-based assertions, and several negative/boundary scenarios are entirely missing.
